Package src.camp_management

Class CampInfo

java.lang.Object
src.camp_management.CampInfo
public class CampInfo extends Object
The CampInfo class represents information about a specific camp, including details about the camp, attendees, committees, suggestions, etc.
Since:
2023-11-26
Version:
1.0
Author:

      public CampInfo(String campName, LocalDate startdate, LocalDate enddate, LocalDate registerDeadline, Faculty userGroup, String location, int totalSlots, int committeeSlots, String description, Staff inCharge, boolean visibility)
      Constructs a new CampInfo object with the provided parameters.
      Parameters:
      campName - The name of the camp.
      startdate - The start date of the camp.
      enddate - The end date of the camp.
      registerDeadline - The registration deadline for the camp.
      userGroup - The faculty group associated with the camp.
      location - The location of the camp.
      totalSlots - The total number of slots available for the camp.
      committeeSlots - The number of slots reserved for committee members.
      description - A description of the camp.
      inCharge - The staff member in charge of the camp.
      visibility - The visibility status of the camp (true if visible to staff, false otherwise).

    • addCampCom

      public void addCampCom(CampCommittee campCom)
      Adds a camp committee member to the list of committee members for this camp. Assumes that the number of committee members is counted into total slots. Prints a message indicating that the student has signed up as a committee member.
      Parameters:
      campCom - The camp committee member to be added.
